The article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 18, 2009, as National POW/MIA Recognition Day. The proclamation highlights the commitment of the United States to never leave any service member behind and to bring missing service members home. It pays tribute to those who have not returned from the battlefield, expresses gratitude to those who returned after facing hardships, and honors the sacrifices made by the families of prisoners of war and those missing in action. The proclamation also acknowledges the efforts of Americans working to identify and recover the remains of fallen heroes and emphasizes the commitment to see them reunited with the land they defended. The article concludes by urging all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.